  "body": "### Description\r\nAs an developer, I want to be able to perfom solidity mapping delete and set operations successfully on hyperledger besu as I can on geth and ganache. \r\n\r\nCalling delete and set to 0 solidity mapping  in solidity fail on hyperledger besu. \r\n\r\nI have posted a simple reproducer of these issues here: https://github.com/cianx/besu-test\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* Calling delete and set to 0 solidity mapping succeed.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n1. Start a besu node, (tested on kaleido network, private clique network, and docker dev node)\r\nThe simplest configuration is:\r\n```\r\n>   besu \\\r\n    --network=dev \\\r\n    --miner-enabled \\\r\n    --miner-coinbase=0xfe3b557e8fb62b89f4916b721be55ceb828dbd73 \\\r\n    --rpc-http-cors-origins=all \\\r\n    --host-whitelist=* \\\r\n    --rpc-http-enabled=true \\\r\n    --rpc-http-host=0.0.0.0 \\\r\n    --rpc-http-port=4300 \\\r\n    --min-gas-price=0 \r\n```\r\n2. \r\n```\r\ncontract TestContract {\r\n  mapping (address => uint256) balances;\r\n\r\n  function setBalance(uint256 amt) public {\r\n    balances[msg.sender] = amt;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  function zeroBalance() public {\r\n    balances[msg.sender] = 0;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  function resetBalance() public {\r\n    delete balances[msg.sender];\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  function getBalance(address addr) public view returns(uint256) {\r\n    return balances[addr];\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n3. Call contract contract functions resetBalance, zeroBalance \r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\r\nSuccess full transactions exection, mapping entry deleted or set to zero respectively.\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\r\nTransactions return a failure code \r\n```\r\ntest_1     |   statusCode: 400,\r\ntest_1     |   responseText: '{\\n' +\r\ntest_1     |     '  \"jsonrpc\" : \"2.0\",\\n' +\r\ntest_1     |     '  \"id\" : 94,\\n' +\r\ntest_1     |     '  \"error\" : {\\n' +\r\ntest_1     |     '    \"code\" : -32003,\\n' +\r\ntest_1     |     '    \"message\" : \"Intrinsic gas exceeds gas limit\"\\n' +\r\ntest_1     |     '  }\\n' +\r\ntest_1     |     '}',\r\n```\r\n**Frequency:** [What percentage of the time does it occur?]\r\nAlways.\r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* Software version: [`besu --version`]\r\n1.4.3 \r\n* Java version: [`java -version`]\r\n* OS Name & Version: [`cat /etc/*release`]\r\nDISTRIB_ID=Ubuntu\r\nDISTRIB_RELEASE=18.04\r\nDISTRIB_CODENAME=bionic\r\nDISTRIB_DESCRIPTION=\"Ubuntu 18.04.4 LTS\"\r\nNAME=\"Ubuntu\"\r\nVERSION=\"18.04.4 LTS (Bionic Beaver)\"\r\nID=ubuntu\r\nID_LIKE=debian\r\nPRETTY_NAME=\"Ubuntu 18.04.4 LTS\"\r\nVERSION_ID=\"18.04\"\r\nHOME_URL=\"https://www.ubuntu.com/\"\r\nSUPPORT_URL=\"https://help.ubuntu.com/\"\r\nBUG_REPORT_URL=\"https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/\"\r\nPRIVACY_POLICY_URL=\"https://www.ubuntu.com/legal/terms-and-policies/privacy-policy\"\r\nVERSION_CODENAME=bionic\r\nUBUNTU_CODENAME=bionic\r\n\r\n* Kernel Version: [`uname -a`]\r\nLinux sterling 5.3.0-42-generic #34~18.04.1-Ubuntu SMP Fri Feb 28 13:42:26 UTC 2020 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n* Docker Version: [`docker version`]\r\nDocker version 19.03.6, build 369ce74a3c\r\n* Cloud VM, type, size: [Amazon Web Services I3-large]\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n",
